<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Cylinder Head and Valves -
        Install - Valve Lever Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010406.3" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Valve Lever Assembly</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010406.3.1">
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert valve lever assembly with long cylinder head bolts in their respective bolt
                    holes.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To prevent possible engine damage, do not install new style valve train components in
                            engines produced with old style valve train components. Replacement of old style valve train
                            components requires complete replacement of all valve train components, including push rod
                            assemblies, roller tappet assemblies, and rocker arm assemblies.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install long cylinder head bolts, the bolts should be run in finger tight (except two
                    end bolts). Place 0.013 mm (0.005 in) Feeler Gauge between outside brackets and rocker levers to
                    prevent binding. Finger-tighten remaining two end bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010477" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8571.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install valve lever assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f210010478" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8284.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Tighten valve lever assembly mounting bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten cylinder head bolts in four stages as specified, see "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_106.xml" xrefid="t210010404">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                    ."
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Check two end rocker arms for freedom of movement after tightening cylinder head bolts.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two 0.013 mm (0.005 in)Feeler Gauges.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>All valves are adjusted by rotating the engine only twice.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate crankshaft until piston 1 is on compression stroke and timing arrow on front
                    cover is in line with TDC mark on vibration damper.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Confirm that piston 1 is on compression stroke by verifying piston 2 exhaust valve is
                            open, valve spring is compressed.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>
                    <title>Alternate Method</title>
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Confirm piston 1 is on compression stroke by removing camshaft position sensor and
                            observing vanes on timing disk plate. When thin vane is visible through CMP sensor mounting
                            orifice in front cover, piston 1 is on compression stroke. Continue turning engine until TDC
                            marks are aligned in front cover and vibration damper pulley. Adjust valves that should be
                            adjusted with piston 1 on compression stroke.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>Set cold valve lash by loosening lock nut. Turning valve adjustment screw with 0.64 mm (0.025
                    in)Feeler Gauge inserted between rocker arm and valve stem tip. Tighten valve adjustment screw until
                    light drag is felt.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010479" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8594.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Set valve lash</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten lock nut once valve adjustment is set.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010480" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8596.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Tighten valve lever lock nut</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Recheck for light drag on 0.64 mm (0.025 in) Feeler Gauge. If too tight or too loose,
                    loosen lock nut and do steps 6 and 7 above.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010406.3.2">
